#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:11
msgid ""
"The Display Panel controls how particles are displayed in the 3D View. This "
"does not necessarily determine how they will appear when rendered."
msgstr ""
"le panneau *Display* contrôle la manière dont les particules sont affichées "
"dans la Vue 3D. Ceci ne détermine pas nécessairement la manière dont elles "
"vont apparaître au rendu. "

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:30
msgid "Draw Method"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:16
#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:56
msgid "None"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:16
msgid ""
"The particles are not shown in the 3D View and are not rendered. The emitter "
"may be rendered though."
msgstr ""
"les particules ne sont pas affichées dans la Vue 3D et ne sont pas rendues. "
"L'émetteur peut cependant être rendu.\n"
" "

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:19
msgid "Point"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:19
msgid ""
"Particles are displayed as square points. Their size is independent of the "
"distance from the camera."
msgstr ""
"les particules sont affichées comme des points carrés. Leur taille est "
"indépendante de la distance à la caméra."

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:22
msgid "Circle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:22
msgid ""
"Particles are displayed as circles that face the view. Their size is "
"independent of the distance from the camera."
msgstr ""
"les particules sont affichées comme des cercles qui font face à la vue. Leur "
"taille est indépendante de la distance à la caméra."

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:25
msgid "Cross"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:25
msgid ""
"Particles are displayed as 6-point crosses that align to the rotation of the "
"particles. Their size is independent of the distance from the camera."
msgstr ""
"les particules sont affichées comme des croix à 6 points qui s'alignent sur "
"la rotation des particules. Leur taille est indépendante de la distance à la "
"caméra."

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:30
msgid "Axis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:28
msgid ""
"Particles are displayed as 3-point axes. This is useful if you want to see "
"the orientation and rotation of particles in the view port. Increase the "
"*Draw Size* until you can clearly distinguish the axis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:32
msgid ""
"Particles visualized like Point, Circle, Cross and Axis do not have any "
"special options, but can be very useful when you have multiple particle "
"systems at play, if you do not want to confuse particles of one system from "
"another (e.g. in simulations using *Boids* physics)."
msgstr ""
"les particules visualisées comme Point, Circle, Cross et Axis n'ont pas "
"d'options spéciales, mais peuvent être très utiles quand vous avez de "
"multiples systèmes de particules en jeu, si vous ne voulez pas confondre les "
"particules des différents systèmes (ex. dans des simulations utilisant la "
"physique des *Boids*)."

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:38
msgid ""
"Specifies the percentage of all particles to show in the viewport (all "
"particles are still rendered)."
msgstr ""
"Spécifie le pourcentage de toutes les particules à afficher dans le vue "
"(toutes les particules sont néanmoins rendues)."

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:40
msgid "Draw Size"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:40
msgid ""
"Specifies how large (in pixels) the particles are drawn in the viewport."
msgstr ""
"Spécifie la taille (en pixels) avec laquelle les particules sont dessinées "
"dans la vue."

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:42
msgid "Size"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:43
msgid "Draw the size of the particles with a circle."
msgstr "Dessine la taille des particules avec un cercle."

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:45
#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:63
msgid "Velocity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:45
msgid ""
"Draw the velocity of the particles with a line that points in the direction "
"of motion, and length relative to speed."
msgstr ""
"Dessine la vélocité des particules avec u ne ligne qui pointe dans la "
"direction du mouvement, et dont la longueur est proportionnelle à la vitesse."

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:49
msgid "Number"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:48
msgid "Draw the id-numbers of the particles in the order of emission."
msgstr "Dessine les numéros id des particules dans l'ordre d'émission."

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:52
msgid "Color"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:54
msgid ""
"The Color Menu allows you to draw particles according to certain particle "
"properties."
msgstr ""
"Le menu *Color* vous permet de dessiner les particules selon les propriétés "
"de particules."

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:57
msgid "Particles are black."
msgstr "Les particules sont noires."

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:58
msgid "Material"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:59
msgid "Particles are colored according to the material they are given."
msgstr "Les particules sont colorées selon le matériau qui leur est attribué."

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/emitter/display.rst:61
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Color particles according to their speed. The color is a ramp from blue to "
"green to red, Blue being the slowest, and Red being velocities approaching "
"the value of *Max* or above. Increasing *Max* allows for a wider range of "
"particle velocities."
msgstr ""
"Colorier les particules selon leur vitesse, La couleur est une palette du "
"bleu au vert au rouge, le Bleu étant la plus lente, et le Rouge étant des "
"vélocités approchant la valeur de *Max* ou au dessus. L'augmentation de "
"*Max* permet un intervalle plus large de vélocités de particule. "

